Unlocking the Mystery of Property Taxes: How the City Determines the Value of Our Homes in Vancouver, BC.
.
.

Hello everyone! As many of you may know, the city plays a crucial role in determining the value of our homes. In Vancouver, BC specifically, the city conducts regular assessments of all properties to determine their value for tax purposes. This process involves taking into account factors such as the size, age, condition, and location of the property, as well as any improvements or renovations that have been made. It's important to note that while the assessment value is used for tax purposes, it may not always reflect the actual resale value of a home. Market conditions, location, and other factors can all affect a home's resale value. By understanding this process, we can better understand our property taxes and how they're calculated. If you have any questions or concerns, don't hesitate to reach out to me or the city's assessor's office for more information.
